HARARE – Three MDC Alliance activists; Harare West legislator Joana Mamombe and youth leaders Cecilia Chimbiri and Netsai Marowa have been granted bail Thursday after they appeared before magistrate Barbara Mateko while in hospital. They were granted $1 000 bail each and will have to report to CID Law and Order once every two weeks. They were also ordered not to interfere with State witnesses. The trio who are facing charges for allegedly violating peace regulations after staging a demonstration in Warren Park three weeks ago. They were allegedly tortured and abducted before they were later found in Bindura. More to follow… 